data.name: labelNotes.Text
data.value: During the installation process you will be asked to choose a configuration type. A database is recommended for typical deployments of the openPG. The openPG Manager application requires a database to function. The web service and XML configurations available to the openPG are typically used in combination with a master database configuration that is maintained using the openPG Manager. For simple installations you can choose an Access database for your configuration. However, Access is not recommended for a production installation and is also not available if you choose a 64-bit installation. Both SQL Server and MySQL are available with versions that may be installed for free.
